\begin_layout Standard
Since its revelation in 2007, the Brazilian pre-salt has brought possibilities
 and ambitions regarding Brazil's energy autonomy.
 The economic impacts generated by this discovery were crucial to revolutionize
 not only the country's energy sector but the economy as a whole.
 With advances in research and development activities for offshore field
 exploration, a race for quick results began, justifying the abandonment
 of past guidelines, such as onshore exploration, partially replaced in
 1966 by offshore exploration 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "dias1993questao"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The decision to explore oil offshore made Brazil assume even greater economic
 risks than those already existing onshore.
 Factors such as wind speed, wave height, current directions, hydrostatic
 pressures, low temperatures on the seabed, and the ductile characteristics
 of carbonate rocks are some of the technical challenges faced for the feasibili
ty of exploration in the pre-salt fields 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "morais2013petroleo"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One of the main discoveries in this region was the Santos Basin, located
 in the southeast of Brazil, covering the coastlines of the states of Rio
 de Janeiro, São Paulo, Paraná, and Santa Catarina.
 Geologically, the Santos Basin is bounded to the north by the Campos Basin,
 near the Cabo Frio high, while its southern border is established near
 the Florianópolis high, in the Pelotas Basin 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "ANP-Rodada-Bacia-de-Santos"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, as shown in figure 1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

